This paper is about automatic structured pruning of deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields of computer science. The most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as these are the areas where deep learning and model compression are most commonly studied. The paper also uses optimization techniques such as ADMM, which suggests that it could be relevant to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves heuristic search methods, which could be relevant to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category.
